(1, 'what-are-self-assessment-tax-returns-in-the-uk', 1, 'articles/YKEKETi0aSpE2cHvE71deLx5sCQtKPANCGgazTcU.jpeg', NULL, 'What are Self-Assessment Tax Returns in the UK?', '<div class=\"content-page\"><h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Non-resident tax refund claim in the UK</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This article guides you to a <a href=\"https://www.mintaccountax.co.uk/self-assessment-tax-return-services\" target=\"_blank\">self-assessment tax return</a> step by step. When you registered yourself as a self-assess taxpayer and in its scheme, also as a non-resident taxpayer in England, now file your tax return. This step-by-step guide walks you through about how to claim non-resident tax refunds. Our list guides you about HMRC for a self-assess tax return. You have the option to meet our team for further professional management and service to the tax return in the UK.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Registered Self-assess Taxpayer rules to abide by</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When you first get registered with the scheme of self-assess tax payment, every year, submit the report of self-assessment. Even if you do not have reached the level of Yearly tax qualifier. The tax year in the UK is starting from 6th April till next year\'s 5th April; however, people also filing their tax returns to not get penalized before 31st January. People should get these services to get all free from the stress of tax issues.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Following are the steps to complete HMRC Tax Return Self-assessment</strong></h2><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><br></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Log into your account, head to the section of income and select Self-Assessment</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Click on Complete Run</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">When you get the welcome message, please read it and make sure that everything matches so then click Start</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Fill all the required details, and in section 3, select appropriate boxes in the section of Tailor your return. Also, don\'t forget to click on Claim other Tax relief\'s box. This option is at the end of the page and then click next to proceed to 5.</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">At step 5, you see that all the information you have filled in the previous page, which generates as a tailor-made tax return for proper form. Different tax concerns are not related to you in some sections so avoid them. Leave all those boxes blank and never enter anything even a DOT (.). There are questions marks by the boxes which show you more information regarding the boxes when you hover your mouse or click them either. There are a few relevant sections at the end of the box as Deductions and Other Tax Reliefs, so fill them, and when you fill everything that is calculated automatically at the end.</li></ul><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p><ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>How we can help you to file your tax return as Self-assess Tax Return</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">One can choose not to get in stress and have their tax issues done and maintained easily in their tax file with maximum tax relief in the UK, even if they are out of the country. One can contact our experts if they like to have assistance in filing their tax returns, and they can also fill the application form for this purpose.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>How to file your Tax Return as Self-assessment</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If it is the first time you are going to file your tax return as self-assessment, it can be bit crossing the fingers, even if you are near to the deadline. There is always plenty of time to submit your file so you can easily claim your tax return. This guide guides you on how to choose the right way to avoid any confusion and mistake you can easily make while online or on papers.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Let\'s guide you:</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">One must apply as early as possible for the Unique Tax Reference (UTR) number that helps to dodge the penalties on deadlines for missed taxes.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Just like a national number for insurance, you also need a UTR number for filing your tax return, and this number stays the same for the whole of your life. You should apply for it as soon as you apply for your first tax return. If you don\'t apply for UTR, you won\'t be able to get the file of the tax return, so you should do it before the deadline.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">UTR number takes just 10 days to generate through email or mail, and it takes 10 days to get activated.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Registered as soon as possible&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The deadline for last year was 5th October to get registered for tax return as self-assessment so you can get your work done from the previous years too. If you get registered late, it\'s not a big deal until you pay your bills on time.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">One must calculate how much tax is due on your, and payment should be submitted by 31st January even if there is no answer to the tax return. There are times when HMRC stretched your deadline for more than 3 months if you get yourself registered late. It is good to pay dues on time, and you can take guidance from our tax agents on handling tax issues and easily avoid all the hurdles for exorbitant fines to pay.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Overlooking your useful documents</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Don\'t overlook the following points:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Date of birth</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">National insurance number</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Address</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">P11D and P60 forms, also P45 if you changed your job last year</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Yearly plan for payment of student loans</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Keep track of your bills for up to 6 years.</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Do not get crossed due to Type of Taxes and its Dues</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Following are the tax one need to worry about</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Income tax</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Dividend tax</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Capital gains tax</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">National insurance</li></ul><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p><ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Please, do not fill the wrong supplement of self-employment</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Fill the supplement of SA103 of self-employment and SA100 tax return of self-assessment. Also, there is a short form if you have turnover around 84,000 or lower than that without any complication in the previous two years. This method is not going to apply to you if this is your first year. So do not forget to ask a professional tax accountant to validate other aspects. </p></div>', 'In this post we have explain about the Self Assessment tax returns. Read the complete post for more information.', 'income,tax,returns', '2019-06-01 15:29:23', '2020-02-13 00:31:55'),
(2, 'can-i-run-a-company-without-an-accountant', 1, 'articles/N4Xblwmyxzu2v5kOruChd8I27unFFM7VQmAbtxFx.jpeg', NULL, 'Can I Run a Company Without an Accountant?', '<div class=\"content-page\"><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You now have plenty of means to aid the most out of accountant problems. For many micro enterprises and <a href=\"https://www.mintaccountax.co.uk/sole-trader-accounting-services\" target=\"_blank\">sole traders</a>, the added costs of hiring an accountant can be returned to the business. When talking with an accountant, you should not talk about fear and nervousness.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Remember a world where your accountant is not nervous or does not feel like visiting a dentist?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Where can your accountant add a minimum of £ 5,041 to your bank account? Protect your payments with a personal assurance?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you pay for your MasterCard prepaid card at Tesco register for full or premium service?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">What if their services can help your children get a promotion or pay for education?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Every time you imagine and do business</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A homeless person in London is exempted from HMRC</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Two weeks of paid work for a young person in East Riding of Yorkshire</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Saved from getting their home from HMRC petition for bankruptcy, etc</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Do you think these Types of Accounts Exist?</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are different types of accountants who add value to your business and last an impression that change lives but they come with a cost. When you have just simple accounting problems and have a low budget, you do not need to talk with an accountant unless you have a big bank account that you can pay to your accountant and run your business. There are many downsides to DIY approaches.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Can you do Accounting for any Limited Company? People will reply instantly, no you can\'t.</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is because of the paperwork, calculations, taxes, and receipts are hard work unless you have any previous experience with the field of accountancy or book-keeping. You are sure that you can do it at any cost no matter what are the odds for your business finances. So, then you can do accountancy of your business instead of hiring anyone.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Single traders mostly have simple requirements for accounting. At the same time, limited companies and partnerships have to face complex accounting procedures and also for filing. If you think you can do it and you fall into the latter category, you certainly do it, but do it properly else you could face penalties from the company\'s house and HMRC.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Limited Company Accounting</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When you have a company with limited liability, then all the assets, liabilities, and income should record in registers with traceable and disclose. The yearly statements finance should be objective and honest, and all the records should show with the following details.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n  <br>\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Assets of business</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Debts of business owed or owed</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Stock owned as inventory at the end of per annum</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Stock takings for inventory</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Bought and sold goods of business</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Spends and cervices of money</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">All the financial records you use to make final accounts, corporation tax, tax return, and taxes that are taxable should note into it. When you have exceeded the threshold of £80,000 of the tax year 2019-2020, you also have to pay your VAT return file and bills of VAT every quarter.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Late Filing Penalties from HMRC</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This information is used by HMRC to find out how much tax your company owes. So the deadline is 9 months and 2 days for paying the tax of the corporation. Just remember that you should pay your tax before you\'re filed for tax return.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you have guts to do you accounting, beware that you do not cross any limit to get penalties. If you have doubts about your abilities in accounting, we recommend you should hire any tax adviser or accountant. This is an extra expense, but it saves you from falling into a false economy if you do on your own.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you fail to file your accounts and do nothing to take off this situation, you could be prosecuted and fined up to £4,000. And, on the late tax return, HMRC will put penalties ranges from £200-10% of the tax that is unpaid. A minimum fine of £700 is incurred when you are late for more than three months.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A good relationship with an accountant can make your company a goodwill company in the market and save you enough time to handle all tax-related hassles. You should check you have a fine-tune accountant who does not take so much salary, so do not rely solely on else\'s words and do your independent search.</p></div>', 'In This post you will be able read about need of an accountant for comapnies. Read the full post for more info.', 'accountant, company', '2020-02-13 00:27:56', '2020-02-19 12:40:33'),
(3, 'how-to-get-register-in-vat-if-you-are-in-uk', 1, 'articles/8ilLwl9NfFq7Y5OTjgWeIGt5KZY4HAiLVdwAGGh5.jpeg', NULL, 'How to get Register in VAT If you are in UK', '<div class=\"content-page\"><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Many businesses can be registered online as a group of companies or partnerships under the VAT number. You can register online in the account, which often known as Government Gateway Account. &nbsp;Then, this is going to submit in HM revenues and Customs (HMRC) for VAT returns.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>With the Help of an Agent</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">An agent can work for you to submit your <a href=\"https://www.mintaccountax.co.uk/vat-return\" target=\"_blank\">VAT return</a> and deal with everything on your behalf with HMRC. When you get your VAT number provided by HMRC, you can easily enlist yourself into an online account of VAT. Select the option of VAT submits returns from the drop down.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">What are the reasons which not make you eligible <a href=\"https://www.mintaccountax.co.uk/vat-registration-services\" target=\"_blank\">VAT registration</a>?</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">When you want to apply for the exception of registration</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">When you want to join any scheme of Agricultural Flat Rates</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">When you like to get register with anybody of corporations like division or business advisory under different number of VAT.</li></ul><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p><ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>You can Register by Posting form of:</strong></h2><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><br></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">VAT1-A when you like to do business in EU business of distance selling to the UK</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">VAT1-B when you import goods more than the worth of £80,000 from any country in the European Union</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">VAT1-c when you dispose of assets when fund claims done on 8th or 13th Directives.</li></ul><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Get Certificate</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It can take longer, but you get your certified VAT registration in 30 days maximum. It can be sent through an online account, or by any agent who registers you or by post at your given address.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>What you must know</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You must provide your bank details, activities, or business and your turnover per annum. When you get to register, that date is your effective date of registration so that you can pay your dues from this date now. It would be best if you were authorized by an agent to get registered on VAT</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>When you Get to Register</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When your VAT taxable turnover threshold goes over £80,000, you must register, or you know that this is your registration point. This taxable VAT turnover is the sum of everything you have sold, which is not exempt from VAT.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Voluntarily Registration</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You can easily register yourself as a volunteer. So, you must get registered for VAT if taxable turnover reaches its threshold of £80,000 in the next 30days or your business had a taxable turnover for VAT of more than the threshold of £80,000 in 12 months. You can also need to get registered when you provide your services or goods and sell them elsewhere.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Outside Business from the UK</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When you have no business in the UK, there is no threshold for you, so you must get register yourself early as soon as you supply any services or goods to the UK in 30 days. If you register late, you have to pay what you owe.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Exceptions</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You can get exception registration if your taxable turnover for VAT temporarily goes over your threshold. You need to write HMRC with proof that you believe in taxable turnover for VAT that not goes over the threshold in the next 12 months.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In this way, HMRC considers exception and write to you as a confirmation letter. If that does not apply, they register you for VAT only.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Taxable turnover of Vat Calculation</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Taxable turnover is the value of everything you provide, which has no exemption from VAT. However, you need to get register with HMRC if your threshold for tax goes over, but this is not fix per annum period like other taxes. It could be any month period when you get register like the end of May or June.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The threshold of £80,000 is limited, and it goes up each year from the 1st of April. UK has a different threshold of buying and selling form other countries like the EU.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>What you Need to Provide:</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When your given threshold is going up in the coming 12 month period, so add all the value of UK sales which are not exempt from VAT, includes:</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Work of building over £110,000 you did in your business</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Loan to customers or goods you brought</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Goods for personal uses or reasons</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Gifts as goods, barter or partly exchanged</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Services as a reversed charge from other countries</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\">It also includes any items that are 0-rated and excludes from sales of VAT or services or goods you export outside the UK.</span><br></p></div>', 'If you are living in UK and you don\'t to know about the VAT registration, then read this post carefully and increase your knowledge.', 'VAT,Registration', '2020-02-17 00:23:56', '2020-02-19 12:36:10'),
(4, 'how-to-find-a-good-accountant-in-london-for-sole-traders', 1, 'articles/m3T6qMr1YJV9DuOKTCOceyU0yvNBRtzU4fFPPfXP.jpeg', NULL, 'How to Find a Good Accountant in London for Sole Traders?', '<div class=\"content-page\"><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Okay, so you just acknowledged the need for an accountant and the haul of finding the account kick-starts. Having a skilled and experienced accountant is essential, and multiple aspects need to be considered. Some of the factors to consider includes their honing of advanced technology and the location. Other than that, check if they will be helpful in reducing the business taxes and what they will charge for the services.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As a company, your primary focus needs to be finding the right person who has a caliber to handle each finance task with precision. While you are in the quest to find the account for a <a href=\"https://www.mintaccountax.co.uk/sole-trader-accounting-services\" target=\"_blank\">sole trader</a> in London, do consider the following points, as they are devised to help you pick out the best one out of the pool!</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Location</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As you are looking for an <a href=\"https://www.mintaccountax.co.uk/london-accountants\" target=\"_blank\">accountant in London</a>, the question is answered right away. However, if you are looking for one in other locations, make sure they are easily accessible to you. However, you will find multiple online services with cloud accounting capabilities, and it is better to opt for them if you find good reviews. Their online presence speaks volumes about their alignment with the latest technology. No matter what the location is, make sure they are able to meet your business’ finance goals in a short-term and long-term game. But again, if you need someone to accompany you to the meetings, opt for the accessible and nearby accountant.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Certifications</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Never fall in the trap of having “skillset,” because the certifications provide a guarantee of them being able to handle the finance tasks for your trade. Every reputable accountant will be flourished with education and will be known as a chartered accountant. These accountants not only have the degree, but the practical knowledge and experience help them develop optimal solutions for you. Whenever they start, they will start incorporating value into your business.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are some people who opt for uncertified accountants, which does more harm than good to their business. So, never make such a move!</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Experience</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">One accountant might be pro at handling the <a href=\"https://www.mintaccountax.co.uk/bookkeeping-services\" target=\"_blank\">bookkeeping</a> and <a href=\"https://www.mintaccountax.co.uk/self-assessment-tax-return-services\" target=\"_blank\">income tax returns</a>, but that doesn’t guarantee if he will be able to handle the sole trading business for you. So, make sure the accountant you choose has experience in the relevant field and has handled the tasks as you are assigning them. The relevant experience will help them cater to the intricate details of your business as they will understand each curve with precision. Moreover, you can check their website for checking their brand history and how far they have come.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Check-In The Friends List</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When you start the quest to find an accountant for your business, it is better to check with your friends or colleagues if they handle the task. But never opt for an accountant even if he has no experience in the relevant field only because he didn’t have a project and needed money. Never compromise on your business because no one can save your business. Moreover, if a company has over ten employees, the accountant for a sole trader will not be the right choice!</p></div>', 'Finding a Good accountant in London for Sole Traders is not an easy task but still possible. So read our guide for more details.', 'Accountant, London, Sole,Traders', '2020-02-19 11:38:03', '2020-02-19 11:46:03'),
(5, 'what-is-an-ern-number-in-uk', 1, 'articles/uiTcdCQsj6msBhLbUjV2CRt0aw4kE4HGoJvL3Gog.jpeg', NULL, 'What is an ERN Number in UK? Lets Have a Look', '<div class=\"content-page\"><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you are the resident of United Kingdom and is running a business, you are highly likely to have ERN which is a combination of numbers and letters awarded by HM Revenues and Customs to make your business identifiable and registered. It helps in giving a unique identity to the business and is also known as employer PAYE reference. There are two parts of the reference which include a reference number along with a three-digit HMRC office number. When you register with HM Revenue and Customs, you will have the welcome pack and will be registered in HMRC.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you are looking for information regarding ERN Number, this article touches every aspect of it. So, let’s have a look!</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>The Importance of ERN Number</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Many businesses and people ask if complying with the ERN number is essential. Well, to answer the question, yes, it is important. Through this number, the government can easily and effectively find out the number of companies and businesses a person has worked with through the Employers Liability Claim. This is more of insurance where employees can sue or claim something against the company. Finding the information through a plethora of books can be pretty exhausting and this is where ERN number will help by identifying the business through number.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Once you register for Employers PAYE, HM Revenue and Customs will award the ERN number. This number eases the claiming process both for the insurers and claimant.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>The Role of ELTO (Employer’s Liability Tracing Office)</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Employer’s Liability Tracing Office is more of a centralized database which is a combination of liability policies and ERNs and is devised with a prime aim to connect the claimants and insurers. The database tracks down the information and makes a connection through the match-up system.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>The Benefit of ERN</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Many people think that ERN is just another piece of paper and a plethora of documentation will adhere to it. But this is a wrong concept as it’s a legal requirement for the businesses to be registered with an ERN number for the sake of claims made by employees during the operational period. With this number, the insurer will need to foot the bill of the claim and you will be free of it.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>The Appearance of ERN</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The ERN is a combination of two aspects; the reference number which is awarded uniquely to each business and the HMRC office number. The HRMC office number will comprise of three digits. There have been multiple modifications in the niche and some of the modifications look like following;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">If the ERN number was issued before the year 2001, 123/A73974 will be the outlook</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">If the ERN number was issued after the year 201, 123/AB829746 will be the outlook</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This number can be located on the PAYE pay-slip booklet which is issued by the HMRC. The number can be applied online and if you provided the correct information, the issuance won’t take more than 14 days.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>In Case of ERN Number Loss</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">First and foremost, add the number to some safe place because, in the United Kingdom, you will need it for tax times but if you have lost it and aren’t being able to locate it, PAYE can help. If you have P60s or P45s, it will be visible there in the form of current and previous employees. You can even get in touch with HMRC online or on the phone and they will let you know your ERN number. However, HMRC will only help if you have a genuine case.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Exemptions</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is essential to be registered with HMRC but if the PAYE threshold is £503.00 monthly or less, you are exempted from it. Moreover, the businesses located in Jersey and Guernsey don’t have to get registered either. However, it is better to consult HMRC if being registered for ERN is essential for you or not.</p></div>', 'This post is all about the ERN number. If you don’t knowmuch about it then just read the complete post to increase your knowledge.', 'ERN', '2020-02-19 13:23:05', '2020-02-19 13:26:12'),
(6, 'how-to-save-taxes-in-partnership-business', 1, 'articles/6K7aWAWXvwG1RSfggp50u8X9gv0JUxgBAa2Vo8GV.jpeg', NULL, 'How to Save Taxes in Partnership Business?', '<div class=\"content-page\"><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Given the dynamic shifts in the business paradigms, the functionality of the business has been made complicated. Topped with the complex taxation services, businesses are shifting to partnerships which devise the need for saving on taxes. There are multiple taxation laws in every country but cannot be complied with by everyone. It’s needless to say that businesses are making huge profits by being in the partnership structure but saving on the taxes is essential as well. So, if you are a partnership-based business, we have got all the tax-saving tips that you need to save some bucks!</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Claim Benefits</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are plethora of people who don’t opt for the home building loans because they don’t understand the benefits adhered to the home loans. When we look at the taxes, businesses with home construction businesses can claim the interest from the property and the deduction can be implied as well. The tax’s gross value will be limited to NIL and in the long run, the taxable income will be low through the setting off approach.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Opt For Cheque</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Every business and household has to pay the municipal taxes and are paid on an annual basis. However, you can claim the income deduction in the case of the property. If you pay the taxes in cash, you are highly likely to lose the receipts. However, if you opt for the cheque, you will be able to keep the record of payments and tax-paying and you can claim the deductions. You can also add it to the bank statement.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Keep Recording</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Never underestimate the power of keeping a record of each expense. Finance has to be the biggest department of any business and it is better to keep everything in check. If you don’t have the proper record, the taxes are likely to increase and you might have to pay 30% to 40% tax, which is insane. Keep all the receipts in a register which will help you claim a deduction.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Evaluation of Stock</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When we are talking about the stocks, they will be valued on the basis of cost but in case of the short-shelf product, it is better to evaluate on the basis of NRV as it has lower costs. NRV is known as the Net Realizable Value which depicts the stock value and ensures that there is zero overvaluation. This will reduce the tax payments to a considerable rate but once you opt for NRV, stay consistent with it.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Depreciation</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When it comes to manufacturing businesses, there are multiple income tax laws that are in favor of businesses such as additional depreciation. For instance, the manufacturing companies have the right to claim an extra 20% of the depreciation on an annual basis.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Source Deduction of Tax</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Income Tax Act has multiple transactions adhered to it and it talks about deducting tax at source while an amount is being paid to the buyer or seller. However, if you fail to accomplish the source deduction, you might see an increase in tax to be paid, which is an adverse effect. So, be careful with it. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Avoid Cash</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When you are making transactions, avoid the cash payments at any cost. For instance, if you make cash transactions more than 20,000 in a single day, you can be exempted from the expenditures through the income tax officers. So, always go for the cheque and avoid playing with cash!</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>File On Time</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you are punctual with the filing of income tax, you will be given multiple benefits such as carrying forward the business income losses. This period can be around eight years. But these benefits can be claimed only if you filed taxes on the due date or before it. So, revise the dates and be proactive about the filing!</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>The Bottom Line</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Each buck that you save is included in your profit margin and these margins matter a lot on the shared and partnered businesses. So, opt for the above-mentioned income tax reduction practices and save on tax!</p></div>', 'In this post we are sharing the info for Partnership businesses that how to save taxes. So read the complete post for details.', 'Partnership, Business,Tax', '2020-02-19 14:58:44', '2020-02-19 14:59:57'),
(8, 'how-to-setup-a-limited-company-lets-have-a-look', 1, 'articles/icK4xpQjiHQIMvXGuGg0n2qbgrm7rFUfrtyY4CLh.jpeg', NULL, 'How to Setup a Limited Company? Lets Have a Look', '<div class=\"content-page\"><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You can quickly get paid on your work if you set up a limited company. You need to define your brand and show what you own in your business. This is the most tax-efficient way to pitch for your work. If you are not sure how to do it, we guide you through the rest of this article. Here is what you need to know:</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>What Type of Limited Company you Need</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When you finalize what kind of company you need to set up as a <a href=\"https://www.mintaccountax.co.uk/limited-companies\" target=\"_blank\">limited company</a>, you should define what type you form. There are two main types:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Public limited company</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Private limited company</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Most of the contractors, startups, and new small businesses go for Private limited companies because they have to share minimum capital of £51,000, two shareholders, two directors and a sectary for the company which must be qualified.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>A Decent Name</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This bit is a fun part and the most fun part of the whole process for new limited companies. Like your web address, your company name must be unique. You can find differentials to guarantee a unique name - for example, a limited company name is \"Limited\" or \"Ltd.\" can use them (for example, \"Park View\" or \"Park View Ltd\"). You can find existing company names on websites to find the best company name, but more than 1,500 companies can be created daily, and the disposal of your preferred name is limited.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Making of a Limited Company</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If the second stage is fun and annoying, then this is another challenging part - of it seems to be. If you\'re organized, it\'s pretty simple. With many online services, you can make a limited partnership company in just a few minutes.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is enough for you to provide your personal information to help the company house recognize you as a company director, and you good to go for your company. In a few hours, the company house will have your limited partnerships up and running.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Completion of Corporation Process</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Companies House is liable for registering every limited company in the UK. More information is available on their website. To complete the registration, you must complete the following documents and give them back to the Companies house. Many times your agent or accountant complete these steps for you:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Memorandum of Association – it has the name of company location and type of business</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Form 10- this form has the name address of the director and address of the limited company.</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Form 12 – This form has all the terms and condition any limited company have under the Companies Act</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Article of Association – this document outline the power of the director, rights of shareholders.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>This is how you become a Limited Company. What else you Need to know?</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are things you need to know and take care of when starting a limited company. Those are all filing and reporting responsibilities that you need to handle by yourself in the first place. &nbsp;You also need a business bank account for your limited company. It would help if you also had business insurance for small business, so you and your business covers what you are doing.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>What is the Cost of Starting a Limited Company?</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The cost of registering a limited company is just £12, and it\'s often completely free when you hire any company to provide you this service. When you take small business insurance, many service providers return your £12. Many banks also offer this refund when you open your company bank account with them.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Responsibilities and Duties as a Director of a Limited Company</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Many detailed articles guide you with your responsibilities and duties as director of a limited company and what you need to file within the given deadline. There are specific duties when you are working as a director of a limited company. This includes:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Your new company must register with Companies House</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Every year, your confirmation statement and annual accounts must be filed.</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Every year, HMRC must have your accounts</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Within the nine-month of the period, the annual corporation tax return should be done, and any tax you owned must be paid before the deadline.</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Personal tax return and registration for self-assessment to HMRC should be done every year (it is not essential when you are running a non-profit organization like a charity)</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">It would be best if you abode by the rules mentioned in the article of association</li>\r\n  <li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Keep reports and record changes updated</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Tell other shareholders if you like to get benefits from any transaction made in the company</p></div>', 'After sharing the post on Limited Company introduction now we have bring the info on how to set up a limited company.', 'Limited,Company,Setup', '2020-02-24 04:05:07', '2020-02-27 19:07:39');
